The Vice President, Mike Pence, visited Spence Airport in Moultrie, Georgia to address the farmers affected by Hurricane Michael. He expressed condolences for those who lost loved ones and acknowledged the devastating impact the storm had on agriculture in the region. Pence assured the farmers that the Trump administration is committed to providing assistance and resources for recovery. He also highlighted the efforts to open up new trade opportunities for American agricultural products. Pence emphasized the resilience and strength of the farming community and expressed confidence that Georgia and the United States will overcome this challenge and come out stronger.